âœ… Best color accuracy and wide viewing angles
âœ… Good contrast for everyday use
âœ… Consistent image quality from different angles

**Cons:**
âš  Slightly slower response times than TN (but modern IPS can still be very fast)
âš  Usually a bit more expensive

**Best for:**
ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ’» Productivity, creative work, movies, gaming (especially higher refresh models)

---

### ğŸ“Œ **VESA (Video Electronics Standards Association)**

This refers to a **mounting pattern standard** â€” not a panel type.

E.g., **VESA 100 Ã— 100 mm** means the monitor has screw holes in a standard pattern so you can use a **wall mount / arm mount**.

So VESA = *mounting support*, not image quality.

